Matter is made up of atoms, each atom consisting of a number of points, really distinct from one another, really without length, breadth, or thickness, and yet really touching each other. Two points do not make a surface, but three do (inchoatively) if the third is not in a line with the other two3 and this is the beginning of the plane, and indeed of all surfaces whatsoever.
